## Git Fork a Repository
### Question : 
Click on the + button in the top left corner and select option Select port to view on Host 1, enter port 8000 and click on Display Port. You should be able to access the Gitea page.

Login to Gitea server using username jon and password Jon_pass123.

There you will see a Git repository sarah/story-blog, fork it under jon user.

### Solution:  

1. Click on the + button in the top left corner and select option Select port to view on Host 1, enter port 8000

2. Login to Gitea server using username jon and password Jon_pass123.


3.  Click on Git repository sarah/story-blog & fork it

